    • Product Description

    Little but fierce

    Z 50 delivers the award-winning performance of Z series in the smallest interchangeable lens DX-format camera ever.*

    *As of 10/10/19.

    Shines in low light

    With a 20.9MP DX CMOS sensor, a robust EXPEED 6 engine and the light-gathering advantages of the wider Z mount, photos and videos shot in low light look clean and professional.

    Eye catching in so many ways

    When shooting photos, Z 50’s outstanding autofocus system can lock onto your subject’s eye and keep focus there, even when they’re in motion, for beautifully focused portraits.

    Unique mood-setting filters and effects

    Z 50 includes 20 high quality Creative Picture Controls and 10 Special Effects, all of which can be previewed in real-time and applied to both photos and videos.

    See more
    See more

    "Selfie" Flip Down LCD

    See for your Selfie

    Flip down the touch LCD to activate Self Portrait Mode—perfect for taking selfies and for vlogging.

    Electronic Viewfinder

    Oh, what a viewfinder.

    High-resolution Electronic Viewfinder (EVF) shows how your photos and videos will look in real time

    Chic ergonomic.

    Form and function in complete harmony.

    Well balanced, deep grip, magnesium alloy construction for sturdy, comfortable & efficient handling.

    Silence is golden.

    When you need to be a fly on the wall.

    Silent Photography Mode lets you capture special moments, wildlife, BTS and more in total silence.

    See more

    4K UHD

    It’s your story. Tell it your way.

    4K Ultra HD and time-lapse, 1080p slow-motion, filters, effects and so much more.

    Slow Motion

    120 FPS Full HD Slow-Mo Video

    Epic 120 FPS slow motion 1080p Full HD video, great for bending time, speed ramping and more.

    Time-Lapse

    4K Ultra HD Time-Lapse

    Jaw-dropping 4K Ultra HD time-lapse sequences recorded as an in-camera movie or individual images.

    In-Camera Trimming

    Trim videos on the fly.

    Shoot a clip, trim it in the camera, send it to your phone and post with the free SnapBridge app.

    How are ratings calculated?
    To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyses reviews to verify trustworthiness.
